Rating: 0
Chili (with an "i") is a mix of chile (with an "e") powder, oregano, and something else, thus is much less spicy. Straight chile powder (with an "e") is simply ground, dried chile peppers - can be very hot, but there are some REALLY nice, more mild chile powders out there. Hope this helps!

